# Linear Integration Rules

## Issue Creation

When user discusses actionable items, create Linear issues:

```json
{
  "team": "WeTest",
  "project": "Linear Automation",
  "assignee": "pelle@weapply.se",
  "labels": ["Development", "<type>", "<tech>"]
}
```

### Type Labels (pick ONE)
- `Bug` - Something broken
- `Feature` - New functionality  
- `Improvement` - Enhancement
- `Task` - General work

### Tech Labels (if relevant)
- `Backend` - Server/API
- `Frontend` - UI
- `AI/ML` - AI-related
- `Integration` - Third-party

## After Completing Work

1. Update issue status to "Done"
2. Add implementation comment
3. Update documentation:
   - **Linear System Overview** (ID: `87ad9c07-f9fe-42fe-8ea6-60c1687548fa`)
   - **REFINEMENT_PLAN.md**

## Example

```typescript
mcp_linear_create_issue({
  title: "Fix attachment detection for emails",
  team: "WeTest",
  project: "Linear Automation",
  assignee: "pelle@weapply.se",
  labels: ["Bug", "Development", "Backend"],
  description: "## Overview\n..."
})
```
